{"id":"341ecb7a74562f344fd84e57d757d00eaaf3f645","url":"https://app.tensormux.com/pages/login.html","title":"Sign in — Tensormux","site_name":"Buzzing","source":"app.tensormux.com","byline":null,"excerpt":"Open models behind one OpenAI-compatible endpoint. Continue with Google Continue with GitHub No account yet? Signing in creates one. Free tier · no card required","content_html":"<DIV class=\"page\" id=\"readability-page-1\"><div>\n    <main>\n      <div>\n        <!-- Decorative: alt is empty on purpose, because the very next line\n             already says \"Tensormux\". Naming the logo too would make a\n             screen reader announce the brand twice. -->\n        <p><img src=\"/img/logo-mark.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"52\" height=\"47\"></p>\n        <p>Open models behind one OpenAI-compatible endpoint.</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <!-- Populated from ?error= when a sign-in attempt fails; the callback\n           redirects here with a coarse reason code. -->\n      \n\n      <div>\n        <!-- Plain links, not buttons: starting OAuth is a top-level GET\n             navigation to the BFF, so this works with no JavaScript. -->\n        <a href=\"/auth/google\">\n          \n          Continue with Google\n        </a>\n\n        <a href=\"/auth/github\">\n          <!-- fill=\"currentColor\" so the mark inverts with the theme; the\n               Google mark above stays multicolor, as its brand rules require. -->\n          \n          Continue with GitHub\n        </a>\n\n        <!-- There is no separate sign-up flow: the provider tells us who they\n             are, so \"have we seen this account before?\" is the whole question.\n             Saying so here pre-empts the \"where do I register?\" bounce. -->\n        <p>No account yet? Signing in creates one.</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <p>\n        Free tier · no card required\n      </p>\n    </main>\n  </div></DIV>","content_text":"Open models behind one OpenAI-compatible endpoint. Continue with Google Continue with GitHub No account yet? Signing in creates one. Free tier · no card required","fetched_at":"2026-07-24T12:36:16.874Z","ok":true,"blocks":[{"html_en":"<p>Open models behind one OpenAI-compatible endpoint.</p>","sentences":[{"en":"Open models behind one OpenAI-compatible endpoint.","zh":"在一个 OpenAI 兼容端点背后开放模型。"}]},{"html_en":"<p>No account yet? Signing in creates one.</p>","sentences":[{"en":"No account yet?","zh":"还没有帐户？"},{"en":"Signing in creates one.","zh":"登录后会创建一个。"}]},{"html_en":"<p>\n        Free tier · no card required\n      </p>","sentences":[{"en":"Free tier · no card required","zh":"免费套餐 · 无需银行卡"}]}],"translated":true,"content_html_zh":"<div class=\"page\" id=\"readability-page-1\"><div>\n    <main>\n      <div>\n        <!-- Decorative: alt is empty on purpose, because the very next line\n             already says \"Tensormux\". Naming the logo too would make a\n             screen reader announce the brand twice. -->\n        <p><img src=\"/img/logo-mark.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"52\" height=\"47\"></p>\n        <p>在一个 OpenAI 兼容端点背后开放模型。</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <!-- Populated from ?error= when a sign-in attempt fails; the callback\n           redirects here with a coarse reason code. -->\n      \n\n      <div>\n        <!-- Plain links, not buttons: starting OAuth is a top-level GET\n             navigation to the BFF, so this works with no JavaScript. -->\n        <a href=\"/auth/google\">\n          \n          Continue with Google\n        </a>\n\n        <a href=\"/auth/github\">\n          <!-- fill=\"currentColor\" so the mark inverts with the theme; the\n               Google mark above stays multicolor, as its brand rules require. -->\n          \n          Continue with GitHub\n        </a>\n\n        <!-- There is no separate sign-up flow: the provider tells us who they\n             are, so \"have we seen this account before?\" is the whole question.\n             Saying so here pre-empts the \"where do I register?\" bounce. -->\n        <p>还没有帐户？ 登录后会创建一个。</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <p>免费套餐 · 无需银行卡</p>\n    </main>\n  </div></div>"}